2:T4cd,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"How to Budget for Driveway Gate Installation Electricity and Servicing in London","description":"Master budgeting for driveway gate installation electricity and servicing in London. Explore power needs, wiring costs, electrician fees, local rates, and ongoing consumption. Save money with expert tips on tariffs and setups today.","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/blog/driveway-gate-installation-costs-london/","datePublished":"2026-03-25","dateModified":"2026-03-25","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://files.autoblogging.ai/images/how-to-budget-for-driveway-gate-installation-electricity-and-servicing-in-london(sezs)_4.jpeg","width":1200,"height":630},"author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Driveway Gates London","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Driveway Gates London","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/android-chrome-512x512.png","width":512,"height":512}},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/blog/driveway-gate-installation-costs-london/"}}5:["slug","driveway-gate-installation-costs-london","d"]
0:["0zc25QUguIxWkQeMj7sNy",[[["",{"children":["blog",{"children":[["slug","driveway-gate-installation-costs-london","d"],{"children":["__PAGE__?{\"slug\":\"driveway-gate-installation-costs-london\"}",{}]}]}]},"$undefined","$undefined",true],["",{"children":["blog",{"children":[["slug","driveway-gate-installation-costs-london","d"],{"children":["__PAGE__",{},[["$L1",[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$2"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Blog\",\"item\":\"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/blog/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":3,\"name\":\"How to Budget for Driveway Gate Installation Electricity and Servicing in London\",\"item\":\"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/blog/driveway-gate-installation-costs-london/\"}]}"}}],["$","$L3",null,{"article":{"slug":"driveway-gate-installation-costs-london","relatedServiceSlug":"electric-swing-gates","title":"How to Budget for Driveway Gate Installation Electricity and Servicing in London","metaTitle":"Budget Driveway Gate Electricity Costs in London","metaDescription":"Master budgeting for driveway gate installation electricity and servicing in London. Explore power needs, wiring costs, electrician fees, local rates, and ongoing consumption. Save money with expert tips on tariffs and setups today.","category":"Costs","publishDate":"2026-03-25","featuredImage":"https://files.autoblogging.ai/images/how-to-budget-for-driveway-gate-installation-electricity-and-servicing-in-london(sezs)_4.jpeg","excerpt":"Driveway gates in London require 24V DC systems for swing gates (500-1500W peak) and 36V DC for sliding gates (2-5kW), with electricity costs varying by tariff and usage patterns. These costs matter f...","content":[{"type":"h2","text":"Understanding Driveway Gate Electricity Costs in London"},{"type":"image","src":"https://files.autoblogging.ai/images/how-to-budget-for-driveway-gate-installation-electricity-and-servicing-in-london(sezs)_1.jpeg","alt":"Understanding Driveway Gate Electricity Costs in London"},{"type":"p","text":"Driveway gates in London require 24V DC systems for swing gates (500-1500W peak) and 36V DC for sliding gates (2-5kW), with electricity costs varying by tariff and usage patterns. These costs matter for safety compliance under BS EN 12453 standards and motor efficiency. London tariffs range from 28-35p/kWh, impacting long-term budgeting for gate installation and servicing."},{"type":"p","text":"Typical power draws for residential automation systems include idle modes under 100W and peaks during operation. Factor in control panel usage, safety sensors, and remote control signals. Annual energy consumption depends on cycles, often adding to operational costs alongside electrician fees and maintenance."},{"type":"p","text":"Plan for voltage drop over cabling distances common in London properties. Use NICEIC power charts to estimate needs for gate motors and automation kits. Consider solar power options or battery backups to offset peak tariffs and enhance reliability during outages."},{"type":"p","text":"Budgeting covers not just installation quotes but ongoing servicing in London boroughs like Westminster or Kensington. Include Part P compliance and NICEIC registered electricians for electrical wiring. This ensures safe, efficient driveway gate operation with minimal hidden costs."},{"type":"h3","text":"Power Requirements for Common Gate Types"},{"type":"p","text":"Swing gates typically need 24V DC motors drawing 50-100W idle and 500-1200W during operation for 3-5m spans weighing up to 500kg. These suit residential driveway gates with low traffic volume. Duty cycles range from 10-30%, affecting overall energy use."},{"type":"table","text":"Gate Type | Voltage | Peak Power | Motor Cost\nSwing | 24V DC | 0.5-1.2kW | £150-£400\nSliding | 36V DC | 1.5-3kW | £300-£800\nBi-folding | 24V DC | 0.8-2kW | £500-£1200\nWooden | 24V/36V DC | 1-4kW (higher torque) | £400-£1000"},{"type":"p","text":"For 50m cable runs, calculate voltage drop using online tools to avoid performance issues. Wooden gates demand higher torque due to weight and friction on gate tracks. Always check gate weight capacity and IP65 ratings for London weather resistance."},{"type":"p","text":"Reference NICEIC power charts for accurate sizing of transformers and power supplies. Integrate safety features like photocells and obstacle detection to meet BS EN standards. Professional London gate installers provide wiring diagrams tailored to your gate opener and control panel."},{"type":"h3","text":"London-Specific Electricity Rates and Tariffs"},{"type":"p","text":"London households pay 28.6p/kWh under Octopus Agile tariffs or 34.2p/kWh fixed with British Gas, with gates adding £25-£85 annually based on 100-300 cycles/month. Smart meters enable off-peak rates around 15p/kWh. Ofgem price caps for Q4 2024 influence residential rates versus commercial ones."},{"type":"table","text":"Tariff | Rate (p/kWh) | Requirements | Notes\nOctopus Agile | 28.6p | Smart meter | Off-peak 15p\nBulb Fixed | 31.4p | No smart meter | Stable pricing\nE.ON Next | 33.2p | Standard | Flexible options"},{"type":"p","text":"Explore solar tariff rebates like Octopus Flux for gate automation, potentially saving on energy bills. Residential gates benefit from lower rates than commercial setups. Track kWh usage with smart metering for precise budgeting of servicing and electricity."},{"type":"p","text":"Factor in ULEZ compliance and congestion charges for electrician visits in central London like Surrey suburbs. Combine with green energy for reduced carbon footprint. Use expense trackers or spreadsheet templates to forecast lifecycle costs including inflation adjustments."},{"type":"h2","text":"Initial Installation Budget Breakdown"},{"type":"p","text":"Expect £2,500-£6,000 total electrical installation costs in London, with wiring at 40% and labour at 35% of budget. This covers cabling from the mains to the gate motor, control panels, and Part P certifications for compliance. Factor in London congestion charge at £15 per day for electrician vans, plus ULEZ compliance to avoid extra fees on non-electric vehicles."},{"type":"p","text":"Typical projects span 2-3 days for residential driveway gates, including swing gates or sliding gates. Trench digging for armoured cable takes one day, followed by wiring, testing safety sensors, and intercom integration. Delays from groundworks or drainage considerations can extend timelines in London boroughs like Westminster."},{"type":"p","text":"Budget for power supply setup, including transformers and surge protection, essential for automation systems. Add costs for concrete foundations if gate posts need reinforcement. Always request VAT inclusive quotes to avoid hidden fees in gate installation costs."},{"type":"p","text":"London gate installers often pass on ULEZ compliance costs for their vans, especially for sites in Kensington or Surrey suburbs. Plan for weekend premiums if scheduling outside weekdays. This breakdown helps with upfront payment planning and long-term budgeting for servicing."},{"type":"h3","text":"Wiring and Electrical Setup Expenses"},{"type":"p","text":"SWA cabling costs £4.50/meter for 50m runs (£225 total), plus £450 trench digging and £180 conduit/termination. Use 2.5mm² armoured cable (SWA) for runs from the house to the driveway gate, buried at least 600mm deep per BS 7671 standards. Include a wiring diagram showing voltage drop calculations limited to 3% maximum."},{"type":"list","items":["Armoured cable: 2.5mm² SWA at £4.50/m x 50m = £225, weatherproof for London rain.","Transformer: 24V 40VA unit at £85, steps down mains voltage for safe gate motor operation.","Trench works: £9/m x 50m = £450, including conduit pipe for protection against drainage issues.","IP65 junction boxes: £45 each, two needed for outdoor connections near gate posts.","Surge protection: £120 device, guards against power spikes common in urban areas."]},{"type":"p","text":"Match cabling distance to gate width and height, whether for steel gates or aluminium gates. Test for IP65 rating on all boxes to handle London weather. Consider solar power options to cut long-term energy consumption."},{"type":"p","text":"Reference BS 7671 for electrical wiring in automation systems, ensuring obstacle detection and reverse on obstruction features work reliably. Groundworks may add costs for uneven terrain or gate track alignment. Get multiple supplier quotes for material prices to optimise your budget."},{"type":"h3","text":"Electrician Fees and Certifications"},{"type":"image","src":"https://files.autoblogging.ai/images/how-to-budget-for-driveway-gate-installation-electricity-and-servicing-in-london(sezs)_2.jpeg","alt":"Electrician Fees and Certifications"},{"type":"p","text":"NICEIC-approved electricians charge £85-£120/hour in London, with full gate installs averaging 16-24 hours (£1,800 total labour). Day rates range from £650 to £900, covering control panel setup, remote control pairing, and safety sensors. Weekend work adds a 50% premium due to demand in residential areas."},{"type":"table","text":"Electrician | Hourly Rate | Area | Part P Cert\nElectro-Fix | £95/hr | Westminster | £150\nGateTech | £110/hr | Kensington | £150\nAutoGate | £88/hr | Surrey | £150\nLondonGate Pros | £105/hr | Central London | £150\nElectroGate Services | £92/hr | Southwark | £150"},{"type":"p","text":"Mandatory Part P compliance costs £150 per job, proving adherence to BS 7671 for building control. London electricians pass on congestion charge and ULEZ fees for service van access. Choose NICEIC registered firms for warranty terms on driveway gate installation electricity."},{"type":"p","text":"Request installation quotes including labour costs breakdown for gate opener testing and battery backup setup. Factor in overtime for bank holidays or heritage properties needing special permits. Competitive bidding from local gate installers ensures value in your electrical certification process."},{"type":"h2","text":"Ongoing Electricity Consumption Estimates"},{"type":"p","text":"Automated gates consume 0.15-0.45kWh daily (50-150 cycles), costing £15-£55/year at London rates. This cycle-based consumption uses about 0.003kWh per cycle for a typical gate motor and control panel. Factor in your daily traffic volume when budgeting for driveway gate installation electricity."},{"type":"p","text":"Peak demand occurs during high-use periods, like family arrivals or deliveries, spiking power draw from the gate opener. Smart meters track this precisely, helping you monitor energy consumption via usage analytics. In London boroughs such as Westminster or Kensington, these tools reveal patterns tied to London weather and routines."},{"type":"p","text":"Solar power options can offset much of this, with 300W panels potentially cutting costs by a significant amount through battery backup integration. Consider solar alongside electrical wiring during installation to lower long-term servicing costs. Experts recommend assessing sunlight hours in Surrey suburbs for realistic savings."},{"type":"p","text":"For swing gates or sliding gates, pair solar with smart home integration for app control. This setup reduces reliance on grid power, especially with IP65 rating components for rain resistance. Budget for initial inverter costs but plan for reduced operational expenses over time."},{"type":"h3","text":"Daily Usage and Annual Power Costs"},{"type":"p","text":"Residential gates average 75 cycles/day (5s/cycle, 0.25kWh total) costing 25p daily or £92/year at 31p/kWh. Low usage suits quiet homes, while high fits busy families or commercial sites. Track cycles with IoT sensors for accurate budgeting."},{"type":"table","text":"Usage Level | Cycles/Day | Annual Cost (£)\nLow (Residential) | 50 | 65\nMedium (Residential) | 100 | 130\nHigh (Residential) | 200 | 260\nCommercial | 500 | 650"},{"type":"p","text":"Costs assume standard London rates and include battery backup draw at 2.5W standby, adding £18/year. Winter heating for de-icers bumps usage by about 20%, common for gate heaters in frosty conditions. Factor this into your installation quote from NICEIC registered electricians."},{"type":"list","items":["Use smart metering for real-time insights, like Octopus tracker tariffs that cut bills through lower rates.","Opt for surge protection and Part P compliance to avoid extra fees.","Plan annual servicing to check voltage requirements and control panel efficiency."]},{"type":"p","text":"For bi-folding gates or electric gate kits, integrate remote diagnostics to predict maintenance. In conservation areas, ensure planning permission covers power supply upgrades. Long-term, use a spreadsheet template for lifecycle costs, including inflation adjustments."},{"type":"h2","text":"Servicing and Maintenance Budgeting"},{"type":"p","text":"Annual gate servicing costs £180-£350 in London, with electrical components representing 60% of maintenance budget. Follow service intervals of 6-12 months as per BS EN 12453 to ensure safety and longevity for driveway gates. London access challenges, like parking restrictions in boroughs such as Westminster, often add to costs."},{"type":"p","text":"Typical breakdown allocates 60% to electrical work and 40% to mechanical tasks. Budget for annual servicing covering photocells, control panels, and gate motors. Factor in electrician fees from NICEIC registered professionals for Part P compliance."},{"type":"p","text":"Plan for London gate installers offering servicing contracts to manage hidden costs. Include emergency repairs and battery backups in your long-term budgeting. Use an expense tracker to monitor inflation adjustments and lifecycle costs for swing gates or sliding gates."},{"type":"p","text":"Consider weatherproofing needs due to London weather, with IP65 ratings essential for components. Service logs help track warranty terms and predict maintenance for automation systems."},{"type":"h3","text":"Routine Electrical Inspections"},{"type":"p","text":"Bi-annual NICEIC inspections cost £95-£165, checking photocells, control boards, and safety circuits per BS EN 12453. These ensure electrical certification and obstacle detection function properly. Schedule them to avoid downtime on residential gates."},{"type":"p","text":"Follow this numbered checklist for routine checks:"},{"type":"list","items":["Visual inspection (£45, 30min) for wiring and connections.","Safety sensor test (£65) on photocells and loop detectors.","Control board diagnostics (£85) for error codes.","Torque settings (£35) adjustment on gate motors.","Certification update (£35) for compliance records."]},{"type":"p","text":"Maintain a service log template noting dates, findings, and photos. Photo documentation proves upkeep for insurance cover and warranty claims on gate openers."},{"type":"p","text":"For driveway gate installation, integrate inspections into your budget. London boroughs require proof for planning permission renewals, especially with smart home integration."},{"type":"h3","text":"Repair Costs for Motors and Controls"},{"type":"image","src":"https://files.autoblogging.ai/images/how-to-budget-for-driveway-gate-installation-electricity-and-servicing-in-london(sezs)_3.jpeg","alt":"Repair Costs for Motors and Controls"},{"type":"p","text":"Gate motor replacement averages £450-£950 (BFT Phobos £550, FAAC 402 £780), plus £250 diagnostics and labour. Common failures hit gate motors and PCBs from power surges or wear. Emergency callouts add £150 plus £95/hr in London traffic."},{"type":"table","text":"Failure Type | Cost (Parts + Labour) | Brands Affected\nMotor burnout | £650 | CAME, Beninca\nPCB failure | £380 | BFT, FAAC\nReceiver fault | £220 | All wireless systems\nBackup battery | £95 | Solar power options"},{"type":"p","text":"Pursue warranty claim processes by contacting gate automation brands with service logs. Compare supplier quotes for trade discounts on replacement motors. Budget for surge protection to prevent repeats."},{"type":"p","text":"In Surrey suburbs or Kensington, factor mileage and congestion charge into repairs. Use diagnostic tools for remote checks via app control, reducing callout fees for bi-folding gates or steel gates."},{"type":"h2","text":"Total Budgeting Strategies"},{"type":"p","text":"Comprehensive 5-year budgeting totals £4,500-£9,000 including install, power, and maintenance for London properties. This range covers driveway gate installation, electrical wiring, and ongoing servicing for swing gates, sliding gates, or bi-folding gates. Plan ahead to manage gate installation costs effectively."},{"type":"p","text":"Lifecycle costing accounts for initial outlay plus operational expenses like power supply and annual servicing. Factor in electrician fees for Part P compliance and NICEIC registered work. Include material prices for gate motors, control panels, and safety sensors."},{"type":"p","text":"Adjust for inflation at 3.5% per year on labour costs, material prices, and maintenance. Use an Excel budget template to track VAT inclusive totals, permit fees, and groundworks. This helps with long-term financial planning for London boroughs like Westminster or Kensington."},{"type":"p","text":"Conduct a break-even analysis for automation ROI, typically 2.2 years at 150 cycles per month. Compare upfront payment for electric gate kits against savings from reduced manual operation. Tools like ROI calculators highlight value in high-traffic residential gates."},{"type":"h3","text":"Cost-Saving Tips and Contingencies"},{"type":"p","text":"Save 25% (£1,200+) by getting 3+ quotes via Checkatrade, choosing solar kits (£1,800 vs £3,200 wired), and annual service contracts (-20% emergency rates). These steps lower installation quotes from London gate installers. Focus on competitive bidding for best value."},{"type":"p","text":"Get multi-quotes via MyBuilder to compare driveway gate installation options. Opt for solar gate kits for 80% power savings, ideal for Surrey suburbs with solar power options. Schedule off-peak installs on weekends for 15% reductions in labour costs."},{"type":"list","items":["Purchase bulk cable from TradePoint to cut costs by 22% on electrical wiring and conduit pipe.","Hire NICEIC Gold members for warranty upgrades and electrical certification.","Secure maintenance contracts from HSS at £165 per year to avoid £400 emergency repairs.","Set aside a 10% contingency fund for hidden costs like trench digging or drainage considerations."]},{"type":"p","text":"Use an Excel calculator template with VAT toggle for precise budgeting. This tracks energy consumption, kWh usage, and inverter costs. It supports financing options like lease purchase while hedging against supply chain delays in London."},{"type":"h2","text":"Frequently Asked Questions"},{"type":"h3","text":"How to Budget for Driveway Gate Installation Electricity and Servicing in London?"},{"type":"p","text":"Budgeting for driveway gate installation electricity and servicing in London involves estimating costs for electrical wiring, power supply setup, gate automation components, initial installation labour, and ongoing annual servicing. Factor in £1,500–£4,000 for electricity setup depending on gate size and complexity, plus £200–£500 yearly for servicing. Always get quotes from NICEIC-certified electricians and gate specialists in London to account for local regulations like Part P compliance."},{"type":"h3","text":"What Are the Main Electrical Costs in Driveway Gate Installation in London?"},{"type":"image","src":"https://files.autoblogging.ai/images/how-to-budget-for-driveway-gate-installation-electricity-and-servicing-in-london(sezs)_4.jpeg","alt":"What Are the Main Electrical Costs in Driveway Gate Installation in London?"},{"type":"p","text":"When learning how to budget for driveway gate installation electricity and servicing in London, key electrical costs include cabling (£300–£800), control panels and motors (£800–£2,000), safety sensors (£150–£400), and professional installation (£500–£1,500). London's higher labour rates and potential for trenching under driveways can increase totals; add 20% contingency for unexpected issues like underground obstacles."},{"type":"h3","text":"How Much Does Annual Servicing Cost for Electrified Driveway Gates in London?"},{"type":"p","text":"To effectively budget for driveway gate installation electricity and servicing in London, allocate £250–£600 per year for servicing. This covers inspections, lubrication, electrical checks, and software updates by certified technicians. Contracts often start at £20–£50 monthly, ensuring compliance with UK safety standards and preventing breakdowns in London's variable weather."},{"type":"h3","text":"What Factors Influence Budgeting for Driveway Gate Electricity in London?"},{"type":"p","text":"Several factors affect how to budget for driveway gate installation electricity and servicing in London, including gate type (swing vs. sliding), power source (mains vs. solar), distance from the property's electrical panel, and zoning laws. Urban London properties may need reinforced cabling for heavy use, pushing costs up by 15–30%; consult local experts for site-specific assessments."},{"type":"h3","text":"Are There Grants or Discounts for Driveway Gate Installation Electricity in London?"},{"type":"p","text":"While budgeting how to budget for driveway gate installation electricity and servicing in London, check for ECO4 grants or local council incentives if upgrading to energy-efficient solar-powered gates, potentially saving £500–£2,000. VAT at 5% applies to energy-saving installations; always verify eligibility through approved installers to reduce upfront electricity costs."},{"type":"h3","text":"How Can I Save Money on Servicing Driveway Gates in London?"},{"type":"p","text":"To optimise how to budget for driveway gate installation electricity and servicing in London, opt for multi-year service contracts (10–20% savings), perform basic DIY checks like debris clearance, and choose durable components from the start. Schedule servicing in off-peak seasons and compare quotes from at least three London-based firms registered with the Gate Safety Association for best value."}]},"relatedService":{"id":"electric-swing","title":"Electric Swing Gates","slug":"electric-swing-gates","description":"Classic double or single swing gates with electric automation. The most popular choice for London driveways with enough clearance in front of or behind the gate.","image":"/images/gates/gate-aluminium-swing-open-luxury-garden.png","icon":"Shield","color":"emerald","faqs":[{"question":"Should my swing gates open inward or outward?","answer":"In most cases, gates must open inward onto your property. UK planning rules generally prevent gates from opening outward over a public footpath or road. If your driveway slopes downward from the road, inward opening can be tricky, so your installer may recommend underground motors or articulated arm systems to manage the gradient."},{"question":"How wide should swing gates be?","answer":"For a comfortable fit, most London driveways work well with a total opening of 3 to 4 metres for cars, or up to 5 metres if you need space for larger vehicles. Your installer will assess the driveway width, pillar positions, and turning angles during the survey. Double gates split the opening into two leaves for a balanced look."},{"question":"Do swing gates need planning permission?","answer":"Generally no, provided the gate is under 2 metres tall (or under 1 metre if next to a highway) and your property is not listed or in a conservation area. Some London boroughs have additional guidelines, so your installer will advise on any local restrictions during the initial consultation."}]},"bottomRelated":[{"slug":"automated-gate-total-cost-london","title":"The Total Cost of Owning an Automated Gate in London in 2026","category":"Costs","featuredImage":"https://files.autoblogging.ai/images/the-total-cost-of-owning-an-automated-gate-in-london-in-2026(oj77)_4.jpeg"},{"slug":"driveway-gate-property-value-london","title":"How a Bespoke Driveway Gate Can Increase Your London Property Value","category":"Buying Guide","featuredImage":""},{"slug":"driveway-gates-noise-reduction-london","title":"Can Solid Driveway Gates Help Reduce London Traffic Noise","category":"Buying Guide","featuredImage":"https://files.autoblogging.ai/images/can-solid-driveway-gates-help-reduce-london-traffic-noise(s67o)_4.jpeg"}],"serviceList":[{"slug":"electric-sliding-gates","title":"Electric Sliding Gates"},{"slug":"electric-swing-gates","title":"Electric Swing Gates"},{"slug":"wooden-driveway-gates","title":"Wooden Driveway Gates"},{"slug":"metal-driveway-gates","title":"Metal Driveway Gates"},{"slug":"automated-gate-systems","title":"Automated Gate Systems"},{"slug":"gate-repair-and-maintenance","title":"Gate Repair and Maintenance"},{"slug":"gate-automation-kits","title":"Gate Automation (Retrofit)"},{"slug":"commercial-gates","title":"Commercial Gates"},{"slug":"aluminium-driveway-gates","title":"Aluminium Driveway Gates"},{"slug":"composite-driveway-gates","title":"Composite Driveway Gates"},{"slug":"hardwood-driveway-gates","title":"Hardwood Driveway Gates"},{"slug":"wrought-iron-gates","title":"Wrought Iron Gates"},{"slug":"pedestrian-side-gates","title":"Pedestrian and Side Gates"}],"articleImageMap":{"bi-fold-vs-sliding-gates-london":"https://files.autoblogging.ai/images/bi-fold-vs-sliding-gates-and-which-system-works-best-for-short-london-driveways(hlz1)_4.jpeg","telescopic-gates-space-saving-london":"","automated-gat